      "seed": 346777353,
      "version": 1146,
      "versionNonce": 1210587111,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1774022529985,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "API Gateway Vs Load balancer\nLoad balancer simply distributes traffic across multiple instances of a microservice based on various factors like health, traffic etc\nAPI gateway has ability to understand an API and then take decision, whatever to route it.\n\nIt has other capabilities like :\n1) API Composition : Different devices show different functionality for same data.\n2) Authentication : API gateway can integrate with validation flow like OAUTH. If successful then only gateway allows to services.\n3) Rate limiting : API gateway can set rules  like managing burst limit, api throttling, ip based blocking, API queues etc.\n4) Service discovery : As microservices can scale up and down, it necessary to know the location. Service discovery keep track of those.\n\nHow API gateway handles millions of request as a single entry point : \nThere would be different regions like in AWS, and different entry point.\nDNS is responsible(like Route 53) to distribute traffic between different region.\n \n\n ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 393,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "API Gateway Vs Load balancer\nLoad balancer simply distributes traffic across multiple instances of a microservice based on various factors like health, traffic etc\nAPI gateway has ability to understand an API and then take decision, whatever to route it.\n\nIt has other capabilities like :\n1) API Composition : Different devices show different functionality for same data.\n2) Authentication : API gateway can integrate with validation flow like OAUTH. If successful then only gateway allows to services.\n3) Rate limiting : API gateway can set rules  like managing burst limit, api throttling, ip based blocking, API queues etc.\n4) Service discovery : As microservices can scale up and down, it necessary to know the location. Service discovery keep track of those.\n\nHow API gateway handles millions of request as a single entry point : \nThere would be different regions like in AWS, and different entry point.\nDNS is responsible(like Route 53) to distribute traffic between different region.\n \n\n ",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
  "appState": {
    "gridSize": null,
    "viewBackgroundColor": "#ffffff"
